<TEXT>&#2;<DATELINE>2007-04-12</DATELINE><TITLE>Human Bocavirus, a Respiratory and Enteric Virus</TITLE><BODY>In Spain, human bocavirus (HBoV) was detected in 48 (9.1%) of 527 children with gastroenteritis at similar frequency as for children with respiratory illness (40/520, 7.7%). Fecal excretion adds new concern about the transmission of HBoV. To our knowledge, this report is the first to document HBoV in human feces.&#3;</BODY></TEXT>